   <head>De Authore. <hi>T. P.</hi>
   </head>
   <l>
      <hi>BLame not his pen, though wanton in his blood,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>Here uels like a Ʋirgin newly marryed:</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>Pollicie is his delight, his streaming flood</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>To that he is married, in that he shal be buried,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>And though he buried were, this nere shall dye,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>And though he banisht were, this nere shall flye.</hi>
   </l>
